WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:07.000
OK, Phillip.

00:07.000 --> 00:10.000
This is your third cup of coffee.

00:10.000 --> 00:15.000
We should get to work, or we won't be finished by dinner time.

00:15.000 --> 00:16.000
I guess we must.

00:16.000 --> 00:19.000
We must.

00:19.000 --> 00:20.000
OK.

00:20.000 --> 00:22.000
Ah.

00:22.000 --> 00:26.000
Mm.

00:26.000 --> 00:31.000
The beginning of my famous Thanksgiving apple pie.

00:31.000 --> 00:33.000
One apple.

00:33.000 --> 00:34.000
Two apples.

00:34.000 --> 00:36.000
Three apples.

00:36.000 --> 00:37.000
Four.

00:37.000 --> 00:39.000
Come on, Phillip.

00:39.000 --> 00:41.000
Get busy with your famous apple pie.

00:41.000 --> 00:43.000
There's much more to be done.

00:43.000 --> 00:46.000
What goes into my apple pie besides apples?

00:46.000 --> 00:50.000
Ah, yes.

00:50.000 --> 00:53.000
Flower.

00:53.000 --> 00:55.000
Sugar.

00:55.000 --> 01:02.000
Butter.

01:02.000 --> 01:03.000
Butter. Nice.

01:03.000 --> 01:06.000
Cold and hard.

01:06.000 --> 01:07.000
OK.

01:07.000 --> 01:08.000
You're the walnuts.

01:08.000 --> 01:13.000
Last but not least, the reason my apple pie is famous?

01:13.000 --> 01:14.000
Cinnamon.

01:14.000 --> 01:18.000
Cinnamon.

01:18.000 --> 01:20.000
Ellen, where's the cinnamon?

01:20.000 --> 01:24.000
There isn't any cinnamon in the cabinet with the salt and pepper.

01:24.000 --> 01:31.000
It's not a good one.

01:31.000 --> 01:39.000
So, pepper, dillweed, garlic, powder, cinnamon, Ellen.

01:39.000 --> 01:40.000
Yes, Phillip.

01:40.000 --> 01:45.000
Is it possible that we forgot to buy cinnamon?

01:45.000 --> 01:46.000
Yes.

01:46.000 --> 01:50.000
It is possible that we forgot to buy cinnamon.

01:50.000 --> 01:55.000
How can I make my famous apple pie without cinnamon?

01:55.000 --> 01:56.000
Good morning.

01:56.000 --> 01:58.000
Oh, hi, Robbie.

01:58.000 --> 02:00.000
Good morning, Robbie.

02:00.000 --> 02:02.000
Can you do me a favor?

02:02.000 --> 02:03.000
Sure, Dad.

02:03.000 --> 02:04.000
What?

02:04.000 --> 02:07.000
Remember my apple pie on Thanksgiving?

02:07.000 --> 02:11.000
What do you love about it?

02:11.000 --> 02:13.000
The apples?

02:13.000 --> 02:16.000
Oh, the cinnamon.

02:16.000 --> 02:18.000
Right.

02:18.000 --> 02:20.000
We don't have any cinnamon.

02:20.000 --> 02:22.000
I'll go down to Henry's grocery.

02:22.000 --> 02:23.000
He's always open.

02:23.000 --> 02:24.000
I'll get some for you.

02:24.000 --> 02:27.000
That's my boy.

02:27.000 --> 02:29.000
Oh, put your heavy jacket on, Robbie.

02:29.000 --> 02:33.000
It's cold outside.

02:33.000 --> 02:35.000
Alexander might call.

02:35.000 --> 02:37.000
Tell her I'll call her right back.

02:37.000 --> 02:38.000
OK.

02:38.000 --> 02:43.000
Thanks, son.

02:43.000 --> 02:47.000
Why does he always have to slam the apple pie on?

02:47.000 --> 02:50.000
He always has to slam the door.

02:50.000 --> 02:54.000
Hello?

02:54.000 --> 02:56.000
Hello, Alexander.

02:56.000 --> 02:58.000
How are you?

02:58.000 --> 03:00.000
Fine.

03:00.000 --> 03:02.000
Robbie just went to the store.

03:02.000 --> 03:05.000
He'll be back soon when he said he'd call you.

03:05.000 --> 03:08.000
Oh, oh, I see.

03:08.000 --> 03:11.000
Oh, certainly.

03:11.000 --> 03:13.000
What old do you have the phone?

03:13.000 --> 03:16.000
Over there?

03:16.000 --> 03:18.000
Oh, I see.

03:18.000 --> 03:22.000
Please, I know he wants to talk to you.

03:22.000 --> 03:24.000
Thank you.

03:24.000 --> 03:27.000
And happy Thanksgiving to you and your family too.

03:27.000 --> 03:29.000
Try to come by later for dessert.

03:29.000 --> 03:31.000
Bye.

03:31.000 --> 03:34.000
That was Alexandra.

03:34.000 --> 03:38.000
She and the Melinas are going to spend Thanksgiving with their cousins.

03:38.000 --> 03:40.000
She doesn't have the phone number.

03:40.000 --> 03:43.000
Robbie, will be disappointed.

03:43.000 --> 03:45.000
He'll be grouchy.

03:45.000 --> 03:47.000
Or maybe she'll call back.

03:47.000 --> 03:50.000
She promised him.

03:50.000 --> 03:56.000
Here's your cinnamon pop.

03:56.000 --> 04:02.000
It was a dollar and sixty cents.

04:02.000 --> 04:07.000
You forgot to ask me for the change.

04:07.000 --> 04:14.000
Or did you forget to give it to me?

04:14.000 --> 04:19.000
Thanks, son.

04:19.000 --> 04:23.000
Alexandra Carl.

04:23.000 --> 04:24.000
I'll call her back.

04:24.000 --> 04:26.000
She said she'll call you later.

04:26.000 --> 04:33.000
She's not at home.

04:33.000 --> 04:38.000
You should have your breakfast, son.

04:38.000 --> 04:39.000
Like you feel better.

04:39.000 --> 04:40.000
Protein.

04:40.000 --> 04:41.000
Lightens.

04:41.000 --> 04:42.000
She said she'll call back.

04:42.000 --> 04:44.000
Yes, she did.

04:44.000 --> 04:46.000
Good morning, everyone.

04:46.000 --> 04:49.000
Happy turkey day.

04:49.000 --> 04:51.000
What's wrong?

04:51.000 --> 04:52.000
Nothing.

04:52.000 --> 04:54.000
Absolutely nothing.

04:54.000 --> 04:58.000
What's gotten into him?

04:58.000 --> 05:00.000
He missed a phone call.

05:00.000 --> 05:03.000
From my...

05:03.000 --> 05:05.000
Yes, Alexandra.

05:05.000 --> 05:09.000
It's nice to see young love.

05:09.000 --> 05:11.000
Oh, to be young again.

05:11.000 --> 05:13.000
Where's coffee?

05:13.000 --> 05:16.000
Where's coffee?

